Two suspected armed robbers, who specialised in robbing Points of Sales (POS) have been caught, butchered and burnt by an irate mob in Yenagoa, Bayelsa State. It was gathered that the two suspects were caught at Green Villa in Biogbolo suburb in Yenagoa while robbing a POS-enabled cash centre. They were reportedly killed by the mob with their remains dumped in their car and set ablaze. A source, who witnessed the incident said: “Armed robbers and thieves were caught, butchered and burnt in hheir car at Green villa Road, Biogbolo, Yenagoa, Bayelsa State. “Luck ran out of the two criminals who went to rob a POS at Green Villa Road, Biogbolo, Yenagoa, with a Lexus Car. They were caught, butchered and burnt alongside the Lexus car they came with”. When contacted, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Asinim Butswat, confirmed the incident and condemned the action. He said investigations were ongoing to unravel the circumstances that led to the incident.